<heading id="B3088105FF8EFFF2FE3418118623B03C" box="[429,887,540,567]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="25" pageNumber="824" reason="5">
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF8EFFF2FE3418118623B03C" authority="(Fieber, 1851)" baseAuthorityName="Fieber" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[429,887,540,567]" class="Insecta" family="Corixidae" genus="Trichocorixa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="824" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verticalis">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF8EFFF2FE3418118792B03C" bold="true" box="[429,710,540,567]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="824">Trichocorixa verticalis</emphasis>
(Fieber, 1851)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FF8EFFF2FF59185C8425B113" blockId="25.[160,1156,593,792]" pageId="25" pageNumber="824">
A widespread North American species that was previously reported from St. Thomas, St. Croix and 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF8EFFF2FEA418798497B086" box="[317,451,628,653]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="25" pageNumber="824">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
, as well as many other Caribbean Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF8EFFF2FC361879817AB086" author="Sailer RI" box="[943,1070,628,653]" pageId="25" pageNumber="824" pagination="289 - 407" refId="ref29687" refString="Sailer RI. 1948. The genus Tricochorixa (Corixidae, Hemiptera). Univ Kans Sci Bull. 32: 289 - 407." type="journal article" year="1948">Sailer 1948</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF8EFFF2FBA4187985B0B0BB" author="Nieser N" pageId="25" pageNumber="824" pagination="135 - 164" refId="ref27836" refString="Nieser N. 1969 a. The Heteroptera of the Netherlands Antilles - VII Corixidae. Stud Fauna Curacao Carib Isl. 28 (1): 135 - 164." type="journal article" year="1969">Nieser 1969a</bibRefCitation>
), it has been introduced to Africa and Europe, where it has the potential of becoming invasive (
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF8EFFF2FEE418B48736B0D9" author="Carbonell JA &amp; Cespedes V &amp; Coccia C &amp; Green AJ" box="[381,610,697,722]" pageId="25" pageNumber="824" pagination="318 - 334" refId="ref23323" refString="Carbonell JA, Cespedes V, Coccia C, Green AJ. 2020. An experimental test of interspecific competition between the alien boatman Trichocorixa verticalis and the native corixid Sigara lateralis (Hemiptera, Corixidae). Aquat Invasions. 15 (2): 318 - 334. doi: 10.3391 / ai. 2020.15.2.07." type="journal article" year="2020">Carbonell et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). We found this species in saline pools and saline ponds at Magens Beach on St. Thomas and on 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF8EFFF2FD3A18D18677B0FE" box="[675,803,732,757]" name="Saba Island" pageId="25" pageNumber="824">Saba Island</collectingCountry>
. The 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF8EFFF2FCC318D1868CB0FE" box="[858,984,732,757]" name="Saba Island" pageId="25" pageNumber="824">Saba Island</collectingCountry>
records are the first from that site.
</paragraph>
